        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 25 at 5:24PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
West Farmington, or 15 miles southeast of Chardon, moving northeast
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Garrettsville, West Farmington, Bristolville, and Parkman.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
